The paper deals with training neural networks using large batch sizes, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments are conducted on image datasets, indicating a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). The use of second order methods and adversarial training suggests a focus on optimization (cs.NE) and potentially generative models (cs.AI). Finally, the use of distributed computing and autoscaling suggests a focus on distributed systems (cs.DC).
